Package: raspi-bridge
Version: 1.0.0
Section: net
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: iptables, iptables-persistent, netfilter-persistent, ethtool, tcpdump, networkd-dispatcher, network-manager
Maintainer: fxtorres22 <fxtorres22@users.noreply.github.com>
Description: Raspberry Pi Cellular Failover Bridge
 Automates the configuration of a Raspberry Pi as a NAT bridge
 between a USB LTE modem and a router for cellular failover.
 Includes interface pinning, IP forwarding, iptables NAT/hardening,
 and NetworkManager profile creation.
 .
 After installation, run 'sudo raspi-bridge-setup' to configure
 MAC-based interface pinning for your specific hardware.
